directions.Direction: Prep Your Turkey:
Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Remove the giblets and pat the turkey dry with paper towels. Set it in a large roasting pan.
Make the Butter Mixture:
In a bowl, mix together paprika, onion powder, garlic powder, coarse black pepper, coarse salt, celery seed, cajun seasoning, and red chili flakes.
In another bowl, mix softened butter, parsley, rosemary, thyme, minced garlic, and the prepared seasoning blend.
Butter Under the Skin:
Gently separate the turkey’s skin from the breast and legs using your hands. Be careful not to tear the skin. Stuff the butter mixture under the skin, spreading it evenly over the meat.
Butter the Outside:

Rub the remaining butter mixture all over the outside of the turkey. Drizzle with olive oil and massage it into the skin to ensure even coating. Use the rest of the seasoning blend to season the outside and don’t forget to season the underside!
Stuff the Turkey:
Fill the turkey cavity with Celery, Carrots,Yellow Onions, thyme, rosemary, sage, lemons, and a Head of Garlic.
Filling the Pan with Veggies:

Add 1 stalk of chopped celery, 1 chopped carrot, and 1/4 of a chopped yellow onion to the bottom of the roasting pan. Toss in some petite potatoes, cut into pieces, and coat everything evenly with olive oil.
Roast the Turkey:
Cover the turkey with aluminum foil and roast in the oven at 350°F for 2 hours and 25 minutes or until the turkey breast hits an internal of 145℉ (63℃).
Baste and Brown:
Remove the foil and baste the turkey with its juices. Increase the oven temperature to 450°F (230°C) and roast for an additional 30 minutes or until the skin is golden brown and crispy .
Check for Doneness:
Use a meat thermometer to ensure the thickest part of the turkey (the breast) reaches an internal of 150℉ (66℃).
Rest and Serve:
Let the turkey rest for 20–25 minutes before carving. This locks in the juices and makes the meat even more tender. (The Turkey will continue to cook while resting)
Carve and serve the turkey. And make sure to save the juices from the pan to make gravy!

directions.Direction: Preheat the Oven:
Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).
Mix the Wet Ingredients:
In a mixing bowl, add the softened butter and granulated sugar. Using a mixer, beat until creamy and well combined.
Add the peppermint and vanilla extracts, followed by the egg. Mix until fully incorporated.
Prepare the Dry Ingredients:
In a separate bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt to remove any lumps.
Combine Wet and Dry Ingredients:
Gradually add the dry mixture to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined.
Fold in the chocolate chips or chopped chocolate.
Portion the Dough:
Using a cookie scoop or spoon, drop dough onto a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, spacing them about 2 inches apart.
Bake the Cookies:
Bake in the preheated oven for about 10-12 minutes, or until the edges are set but the centers are still soft.
Add the Peppermint Topping:
Once the cookies are almost done, remove them from the oven and sprinkle the crushed peppermint on top. Return the cookies to the oven for an additional minute to melt the peppermint slightly.
Cool and Enjoy:
Allow the cookies to cool on the baking sheet for a few minutes before transferring them to a wire rack to cool completely.
For an extra festive touch, you can sprinkle additional crushed peppermint on top once they are cool.
Serve:
Enjoy your chocolate peppermint cookies with a glass of milk or your favorite beverage!
